<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Archive wall, column five, first two courses. The upper right hand block is badly damaged, but partly reconstructed from fragments found fallen. The lower right hand block is almost completely lost. Loose fragment a (<measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.10</measure> x  <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.12</measure> x  <measure dim="depth" type="length" unit="metre">0.08</measure>)</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p>Inscribed area surviving, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">1.58</measure> x <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.57</measure>. Outspacing for new paragraphs in ll.1, 6. Loose fragment a from the right side of the text, ll. 10-12.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>second to third centuries A.D.; ave <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.02</measure>; ligatures: <foreign lang="grc">ΜΕ</foreign> l.3; apices, ll.1, 2; Heightened initial epsilon at the beginning of l.6. Tall initial <foreign lang="grc">Υ</foreign> in <foreign lang="grc">υἱωνός</foreign>, l.1, perhaps to cover an erroneous iota.</p>
</div>
